"Oh yes!" Malice said sarcastically,"I have been dying to know that!  I didn't think I could go on without that information!  Oh, what a revelation."
Malice chuckled to himself and walked to his room.  He climbed in the hammock, sparing the bed if Wolfblade decided to accept the free bed.  He wormed around in the net, finally getting comfotable.  He drifted to sleep shortly thereafter.

shadowess_azogoth <shadowess_azogoth@...> wrote:
Wolfblade::

She decided perhaps he was right. "Well, perhaps a nap. But back to 
your room? You just want to find out if I snore in wolf mode. Then 
you'll have black mail material on me to hold against me the rest of 
my life. Well pal, I don't think so. I don't snore, so there."

"In the name of God, I banish these souls of the evil undead into damnation.  May God have mercy, for I have none.  In Jesus' Holy Name, Amen." -Rawl, Hellsing-RPG
